Installation on Linux/Unix/Mac:
-------------------------------

Prerequisites:
- Python
- Git

Optional (for viewing artifacts):
- dot, for viewing .dot files
- Word processor supporting Open Document Format Text files (.odt)
- Spreadsheet for viewing .csv files

The following assumes all commands run from home directory, amend as necassary).
1. Run "git clone git://github.com/oliverfields/reqy.git" to download
2. Add "reqy" directory to PATH (e.g. if bash add "PATH=$PATH:$HOME/reqy" .bashrc or .bash_profile)
3. Reload environment (e.g. if bash run ". $HOME/.bashrc" or restart terminal)


Installation on Windows:
------------------------

Reqy will only run on Windows in a Cygwin shell.

Prerequisites:
- Cygwin with Python and Git packages installed

Optional (for viewing artifacts):
- dot, for viewing .dot files
- Word processor supporting Open Document Format Text files (.odt)
- Spreadsheet for viewing .csv files

The following assumes all commands run from Cygwins home directory, amend as necassary).
1. Start Cygwin terminal
2. Run "git clone git://github.com/oliverfields/reqy.git" to download
3. Add "reqy" directory to PATH, add "PATH=$PATH:$HOME/reqy" to .bash_profile
4. Restart Cygwin terminal or source (reload) environment (run ". $HOME/.bash_profile")
